{{Top|leg}}
'''Cirrifog''' was the term applied to unique microcrystals found in [[Monor II]]'s [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]]. Thick and [[Pearl/Legends|pearlescent]], they caused the [[Atmosphere/Legends|air]] of the [[Planet/Legends|world]] to be dangerous for most [[Sentience/Legends|sentients]] to breathe&mdash;billions of the crystals could be found in any given cubic [[Meter/Legends|meter]] of atmosphere. Naturally, the [[Sunesi]], [[Homeworld/Legends|native]] to Monor II, adapted to their environment; so much so, in fact, that young Sunesi would die without the cirrifog. During their metamorphosis into adults, juveniles actually used the crystals to create a sort of cocoon.

When [[Eujustus Kline]] discovered cirrifog, the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] immediately began [[Mining/Legends|mining]] the minerals. With the youth of Monor II threatened by the depletion of the cirrifog, [[Agapos the Ninth]] openly objected to the Empire's actions&mdash;earning him a [[Death/Legends|death]] sentence.

